  "prompt": "My viber on PC doesnt connect to internet. whats the problem? It shows me the messages that other send me but I cant reply through my pc.",
  "response": "Okay, let's troubleshoot why your Viber on PC can't send messages, even though it seems to receive them. Here's a breakdown of potential causes and solutions:\n\n**1. Basic Connectivity Issues (Check These First):**\n\n*   **Internet Connection on PC:**\n    *   **Verify your internet connection:** Open a web browser and try to visit a website.  If you can't browse, the issue isn't with Viber, but with your computer's internet connection.\n    *   **Restart your Router/Modem:** Power cycle your router and modem. Unplug them, wait 30 seconds, plug the modem back in, wait for it to connect, then plug the router back in.\n    *   **Check Wi-Fi/Ethernet:** Make sure you are connected to the correct Wi-Fi network or that your Ethernet cable is securely plugged in.  Try switching between Wi-Fi and Ethernet to see if that makes a difference.\n\n*   **Viber Connection Indicator:**\n    *   Within the Viber app on your PC, look for a connection status indicator. It's usually in the lower-left or lower-right corner.  Does it say \"Connected,\" \"Connecting,\" or something else (like \"No Internet Connection\")?\n\n**2. Viber-Specific Problems:**\n\n*   **Viber is Not Active:**\n    *   The most common reason for Viber not sending messages is that the account is not active on PC\n    *   Open Viber on your Mobile, then PC\n    *   Click on your Profile Picture\n    *   Select 'Account'\n    *   Press 'Desktop and Tablets'\n    *   Select 'Activate Viber on Desktop'\n\n*   **Viber Needs Update:**\n    *   Check for updates: Open the Microsoft Store (if you downloaded Viber there) or the Viber website to see if there's a newer version available.  Outdated versions can have compatibility issues.\n\n*   **Viber App is Busy:**\n    *   Close other heavy programs that may be using the internet and causing delays.\n\n*   **Viber Server Issues:**\n    *   Rare, but possible:  Viber's servers might be experiencing temporary problems. Check the Viber website or social media for any announcements about outages.\n\n*   **Viber Mobile Connection:**\n    *   Make sure that you are connected to the internet on your phone. Viber Desktop can use the mobile to send messages.\n\n**3. Firewall and Antivirus Issues:**\n\n*   **Firewall Blocking Viber:**\n    *   Your firewall might be blocking Viber's access to the internet.\n    *   **Windows Firewall:**\n        *   Search for \"Firewall\" in the Windows search bar.\n        *   Click on \"Firewall & network protection.\"\n        *   Click on \"Allow an app through firewall.\"\n        *   Click \"Change settings.\"\n        *   Find Viber in the list.  Make sure both \"Private\" and \"Public\" are checked.  If Viber isn't in the list, click \"Allow another app...\" and browse to the Viber executable file (usually in `C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Viber`).\n    *   **Third-Party Firewall:**  If you use a third-party firewall (like Norton, McAfee, etc.), check its settings to ensure Viber is allowed.  Temporarily disabling the firewall (only for testing purposes!) can help determine if it's the culprit.  **Remember to re-enable your firewall immediately after testing.**\n\n*   **Antivirus Interference:**\n    *   Your antivirus software might be interfering with Viber's connection.  Similar to the firewall, check your antivirus settings to make sure Viber is whitelisted or allowed.  Temporarily disabling your antivirus (again, for testing only and re-enable immediately after) can help diagnose this.\n\n**4. Proxy Settings:**\n\n*   **Proxy Server Configuration:**\n    *   If you use a proxy server, make sure Viber is configured to use it correctly.\n    *   **Check Windows Proxy Settings:**\n        *   Search for \"Proxy settings\" in the Windows search bar.\n        *   Make sure \"Automatically detect settings\" is enabled, or manually configure the proxy settings if required.\n    *   **Viber Doesn't Usually Have Proxy Settings:** Viber usually uses the system's proxy settings.  If you *don't* use a proxy, make sure the Windows proxy settings are *not* configured to use one.\n\n**5. Reinstall Viber:**\n\n*   **Clean Reinstallation:**\n    *   If none of the above solutions work, try completely uninstalling and reinstalling Viber.\n    *   **Uninstall:** Go to \"Apps & Features\" in Windows settings, find Viber, and uninstall it.\n    *   **Delete Leftover Files:**  Manually delete any remaining Viber folders in these locations (if they exist):\n        *   `C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Viber`\n        *   `C:\\Users\\[Your Username]\\AppData\\Roaming\\Viber`\n        *   `C:\\Users\\[Your Username]\\AppData\\Local\\Viber`\n    *   **Reinstall:** Download the latest version of Viber from the official Viber website and install it.\n\n**6. Contact Viber Support:**\n\n*   If you've tried all the above and still have problems, contact Viber support directly.  They may have specific solutions or be aware of issues affecting certain users.\n\n**Troubleshooting Steps - In Order:**\n\n1.  **Internet Connection:** Verify internet connectivity on your PC by opening a web browser and loading a website.\n2.  **Check Viber Status on Mobile and PC:** Make sure that Viber on your phone is connected to the internet. Activate Viber on Desktop through your Mobile.\n3.  **Restart PC and Router:** Simplest solution, often effective.\n4.  **Update Viber:** Check for updates in the Microsoft Store or on the Viber website.\n5.  **Firewall/Antivirus:** Check firewall and antivirus settings, temporarily disabling them for testing (remember to re-enable!).\n6.  **Proxy Settings:** Verify proxy settings if applicable.\n7.  **Reinstall Viber:** Perform a clean reinstallation.\n8.  **Contact Viber Support:** As a last resort.\n\nGood luck! I hope one of these solutions resolves your Viber issue.\n",
